newsitem.title: USA: Central Maine 619 MW oil-fired unit back.
newsitem.headline: Central Maine 619 MW oil-fired unit back.

text.p: Central Maine Power Co said Wednesday the 619 megawatt (MW) Wyman 4 generating unit, as expected, resumed operation Tuesday following its seasonal maintenance outage.
"It was back up. It went up to full load yesterday. Everything went smoothly," a company spokeswoman said.
The power unit in Yarmouth, Maine, which consumes residual fuel oil to produce electricity, was shut October 5.
Central Maine Power is the operator and majority owner of the Wyman 4 generating station.
